public class LargestSmallest
{
public static void main (String[] args)
int[] numbers ={3,5,7,2,8,-1,4};
int largest = numbers[0];
int smallest = numbers[0];
for(int num : numbers) 
{
if (num > largest)
{
largest =num;
}
else if (num < smallest)
{
smallest = num;
}
}
System.out.println("Largest: "+largest);
System.out.println("Smallest: "+smallest);
}
}

Explanation:
 int largest = numbers[0]; and int smallest = numbers[0]: These variables are
initialized with the first element of the array to track the largest and smallest
numbers.
 for (int num : numbers): This loop iterates through each element in the array.
 if (num > largest): If the current number is greater than `largest`, update `largest`
with the current number.
 else if (num < smallest): If the current number is smaller than `smallest`, update
`smallest`.
 Finally, it prints the largest and smallest numbers.
